'''Simon Willamson''' was the puppeteer for [[Maximilian Rebo|Max Rebo]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. He was uncredited. In the 1980s Simon was one of the leading animatronic creature performers in the UK, working with [[Wikipedia:Jim Henson|Jim Henson]] and [[George Lucas]] on high budget films, including playing Max Rebo, as well as the [[Gamorrean]] Guard [[Jubnuk]], who gets eaten by the [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|rancor]]. He also played a [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] and supported [[Mike Quinn]]'s performance as [[Nien Nunb]] by puppeteering the character's eye blinks.

